+CU and iterated/two-step weighting are *asymptotically equivalent*
+but not identical in finite samples (=CLAUDE.md=, point 4). Emu-GMM v1
+makes CU the default; =IteratedWeighting= exists for legacy
+reproducibility (e.g. ManifoldGMM-trained pickles that consumed
+=weighting_iterations= / =weighting_tol=). See the convergence caveat
+in =IteratedWeighting='s docstring: iterated GMM is not guaranteed to
+be a contraction on misspecified models, and a non-converged solve is
+surfaced via =result.diagnostics= rather than raising.
 
